Requirements:
- Login page
- Auth context/hook
- Token storage isolated in one module
- API client Authorization header
- Logout button
- Protected routes
- Role-aware navigation
- Admin page for users and audit logs
- If auth disabled, dashboard may run in dev mode
- If backend returns 401, redirect to login
- Do not show admin nav to non-admin users

Admin page must show:
- current user
- user table
- create user form
- activate/deactivate user action
- audit log table
- filter audit logs by action/resource/user

Safety:
- Never show password hashes.
- Never show JWT secret.
- Never show API tokens.
- Show warning when default admin credentials are detected.

Frontend validation:
cd frontend
source ~/.nvm/nvm.sh
nvm use 20
npm test
npm run build

Backend validation:
cd ../backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
